1
00:00:05,801 --> 00:00:07,441
(Child actors were accompanied
by a guardian...)

2
00:00:07,501 --> 00:00:08,971
(and filmed in a safe,
supervised environment.)

3
00:00:10,171 --> 00:00:14,311
<i>The one who left her love behind</i>

4
00:00:31,261 --> 00:00:32,261
Why...

5
00:00:36,131 --> 00:00:37,831
- Are you in a lot of pain?
- Yes.

6
00:00:37,831 --> 00:00:39,201
Oh, no.

7
00:00:40,001 --> 00:00:42,371
I think it might be a fracture.

8
00:00:42,671 --> 00:00:45,711
You should see an orthopedist
instead of getting acupuncture.

9
00:00:48,681 --> 00:00:49,681
That day...

10
00:00:50,481 --> 00:00:51,811
The patient with the fracture?

11
00:01:08,131 --> 00:01:09,171
Osteomyelitis?

12
00:01:10,871 --> 00:01:12,271
It's nothing serious.

13
00:01:12,901 --> 00:01:14,471
If it wasn't serious,

14
00:01:14,901 --> 00:01:17,271
why would you call after saying
you'd never contact me again?

15
00:01:19,281 --> 00:01:20,581
Pretty shameless of me, right?

16
00:01:23,611 --> 00:01:24,951
You must be really desperate.

17
00:01:26,621 --> 00:01:27,751
How bad is it?

18
00:01:28,791 --> 00:01:30,291
I need surgery,

19
00:01:31,051 --> 00:01:33,261
and they say I'll have to be
in the hospital for a long time.

20
00:01:33,361 --> 00:01:36,831
What? How could you just
let it get this bad?

21
00:01:37,091 --> 00:01:39,131
Life's been tough.

22
00:01:39,831 --> 00:01:41,201
My wife is sick, too.

23
00:01:41,961 --> 00:01:43,101
And I have kids.

24
00:01:43,701 --> 00:01:44,901
It's okay if you say no.

25
00:01:45,231 --> 00:01:47,941
I've already asked my boss
for an advance.

26
00:01:48,911 --> 00:01:51,811
And I'm not asking for a handout.

27
00:01:53,141 --> 00:01:54,281
I'm asking to borrow it.

28
00:01:55,551 --> 00:01:57,251
I swear I'll pay you back.

29
00:02:08,861 --> 00:02:10,391
My gosh. Honey!

30
00:02:10,461 --> 00:02:11,591
(3H Acupressure Bed)

31
00:02:11,961 --> 00:02:13,101
What are you doing here?

32
00:02:14,301 --> 00:02:17,531
You left this manual
in my dad's office.

33
00:02:18,031 --> 00:02:19,271
I'm so scatterbrained.

34
00:02:20,001 --> 00:02:21,241
Thanks, honey.

35
00:02:22,001 --> 00:02:23,011
Sure.

36
00:02:23,511 --> 00:02:27,111
You should've been here already,
even on foot.

37
00:02:27,781 --> 00:02:28,811
You're a little late.

38
00:02:29,981 --> 00:02:31,881
I had to stop by the bank
on the way.

39
00:02:32,151 --> 00:02:33,151
Want to come in?

40
00:02:33,521 --> 00:02:35,451
No, I've got to get going.

41
00:02:36,151 --> 00:02:39,261
- Okay, take care, honey.
- You're picking me up later, right?

42
00:02:40,191 --> 00:02:41,891
Yes. See you.

43
00:02:44,561 --> 00:02:46,601
Go on, honey. Bye.

44
00:02:53,941 --> 00:02:56,441
(3H Acupressure Bed)

45
00:03:04,681 --> 00:03:06,551
Ju Ah is coming out later.

46
00:03:16,691 --> 00:03:17,761
The props went in here, right?

47
00:03:19,401 --> 00:03:20,561
This is...

48
00:03:20,631 --> 00:03:22,531
Yes, this is
Dr. Han Seong Mi's phone.

49
00:03:22,971 --> 00:03:24,231
Is this Ms. Han Seong Mi's phone?

50
00:03:25,001 --> 00:03:28,071
Yes, who's calling?
I'm her daughter. You can tell me.

51
00:03:28,801 --> 00:03:30,071
You're her daughter.

52
00:03:30,071 --> 00:03:31,811
This is
Myungjin University Hospital.

53
00:03:32,281 --> 00:03:36,211
We're calling about
her breast cancer surgery.

54
00:04:30,501 --> 00:04:33,801
All right, five minutes to showtime.
Everyone to your places, please.

55
00:04:34,271 --> 00:04:36,971
- Models, please stand by.
- Got it.

56
00:04:40,441 --> 00:04:41,641
All right, let's go.

57
00:04:44,951 --> 00:04:47,321
Are you ready? Dr. Han Seong Mi...

58
00:04:48,621 --> 00:04:49,621
Wait.

59
00:04:50,591 --> 00:04:51,591
Mom.

60
00:04:52,961 --> 00:04:54,391
- What?
- What?

61
00:04:58,391 --> 00:04:59,731
Why is everyone so shocked?

62
00:05:00,301 --> 00:05:01,361
She's my mom.

63
00:05:02,471 --> 00:05:03,701
- My gosh.
- No way.

64
00:05:04,501 --> 00:05:06,401
So the truth finally comes out.

65
00:05:06,841 --> 00:05:08,371
Hey, you knew?

66
00:05:08,771 --> 00:05:09,911
Is it that big of a deal?

67
00:05:10,241 --> 00:05:12,611
I'm more surprised that you knew
and didn't say anything.

68
00:05:12,911 --> 00:05:14,011
I can keep a secret.

69
00:05:14,011 --> 00:05:15,311
- Yes, for about a nanosecond.
- Hey!

70
00:05:16,111 --> 00:05:17,751
Mom, you ready?

71
00:05:18,281 --> 00:05:20,051
Don't be too nervous.

72
00:05:21,221 --> 00:05:22,351
What's gotten into you?

73
00:05:22,921 --> 00:05:24,721
You said you hated
being my daughter.

74
00:05:25,121 --> 00:05:29,091
It's just...
I'm so proud of you today...

75
00:05:29,361 --> 00:05:30,831
that I just couldn't hold it in.

76
00:05:32,291 --> 00:05:34,031
I'll do great. Don't worry.

77
00:05:35,061 --> 00:05:37,171
I'm Han Seong Mi, remember?

78
00:05:39,241 --> 00:05:40,241
Right.

79
00:05:41,741 --> 00:05:43,571
Let's kill it today.

80
00:05:54,951 --> 00:05:56,891
By the way, I don't see
the Vice President.

81
00:05:59,761 --> 00:06:03,061
What? Director, over there.

82
00:06:08,801 --> 00:06:11,131
(Fantom Launching Show)

83
00:06:28,051 --> 00:06:29,051
Mr. Chairman.

84
00:06:59,751 --> 00:07:00,881
What happened?

85
00:07:03,891 --> 00:07:05,651
(Inpatient card:
Hwangbo - Hoon, Age 79)

86
00:07:11,131 --> 00:07:13,731
(Hanguk University Hospital)

87
00:07:16,071 --> 00:07:18,471
(Strict Bed Rest)

88
00:07:18,571 --> 00:07:20,701
What brings you here on a weekday?

89
00:07:20,771 --> 00:07:22,271
(Strict Bed Rest)

90
00:07:22,341 --> 00:07:23,371
I just felt like coming.

91
00:07:24,371 --> 00:07:25,541
I was feeling cooped up.

92
00:07:26,981 --> 00:07:30,481
- He hasn't been responsive lately.
- Tell me about it.

93
00:07:30,951 --> 00:07:33,281
He used to say a few words
every now and then.

94
00:07:39,691 --> 00:07:42,591
(Strict Bed Rest)

95
00:07:45,091 --> 00:07:46,161
Dad.

96
00:07:47,031 --> 00:07:49,371
You're not really going to die
like this, are you?

97
00:07:50,901 --> 00:07:54,101
You wouldn't leave me all alone
like this, would you?

98
00:07:57,611 --> 00:07:59,511
Dad, what am I supposed to do?

99
00:08:01,181 --> 00:08:03,151
This is killing me.

100
00:08:03,881 --> 00:08:05,551
I worked so hard to bring
Pacu Nacho into the company,

101
00:08:05,551 --> 00:08:07,951
and Director Baek wants him gone.

102
00:08:07,951 --> 00:08:11,821
My mind's gone completely blank.
What do I do?

103
00:08:13,061 --> 00:08:14,061
Dad.

104
00:08:16,291 --> 00:08:18,961
Dad, please wake up.

105
00:08:19,601 --> 00:08:23,901
Will you let the division you loved
go down the drain?

106
00:08:26,401 --> 00:08:27,441
Dad.

107
00:08:28,641 --> 00:08:29,771
Daddy.

108
00:08:30,841 --> 00:08:32,211
Daddy...

109
00:08:41,951 --> 00:08:45,491
What was that?
Dad, are your eyes open?

110
00:08:45,891 --> 00:08:47,061
Are you conscious?

111
00:08:48,721 --> 00:08:49,861
Whiskey.

112
00:08:50,631 --> 00:08:51,631
What?

113
00:08:53,731 --> 00:08:55,801
It's a 30-year-old.

114
00:09:01,641 --> 00:09:03,571
He woke up to the smell of whiskey?

115
00:09:04,371 --> 00:09:05,371
Yes.

116
00:09:13,651 --> 00:09:15,381
(Fantom, Golf and Sports)

117
00:09:19,291 --> 00:09:20,721
I'm Gong Ju Ah,

118
00:09:20,721 --> 00:09:23,731
FG's fashion therapist
and creative director for this show.

119
00:09:28,431 --> 00:09:29,431
This is awesome.

120
00:09:31,931 --> 00:09:35,371
Caring for the hearts of our wearers
and creating happiness.

121
00:09:35,441 --> 00:09:37,971
The FG 2026 Hot Summer Collection.

122
00:09:38,641 --> 00:09:42,111
We begin with Dr. Han Seong Mi,
who prescribes love.

123
00:09:42,611 --> 00:09:44,381
- Let's go.
- Let's go!

124
00:09:44,451 --> 00:09:45,921
- Let's go.
- Let's go!

125
00:09:45,951 --> 00:09:46,951
Let's go!

126
00:09:48,151 --> 00:09:49,221
Let's go!

127
00:10:09,001 --> 00:10:10,111
- Nice!
- Yes!

128
00:10:36,501 --> 00:10:38,231
- This is actually really good.
- I know.

129
00:11:17,541 --> 00:11:18,541
So impressive.

130
00:11:44,331 --> 00:11:45,731
- You all worked so hard.
- Thank you.

131
00:11:45,731 --> 00:11:46,771
- Thank you.
- Thank you so much, really.

132
00:11:46,841 --> 00:11:48,971
You're on another level.
Truly the best.

133
00:11:51,671 --> 00:11:52,981
- Yes.
- Thank you.

134
00:11:52,981 --> 00:11:54,741
Yes, you did a wonderful job.

135
00:11:54,741 --> 00:11:57,951
- My gosh, I'm a huge fan.
- Thank you. And your name is?

136
00:11:58,011 --> 00:12:00,821
- I'm Yoo Ha Ru.
- Right, Ha Ru.

137
00:12:01,521 --> 00:12:03,021
- Yes.
- Thank you.

138
00:12:03,091 --> 00:12:04,691
- Great work.
- Thanks.

139
00:12:13,531 --> 00:12:16,931
Congratulations, Ju Ah.
A very successful debut.

140
00:12:17,401 --> 00:12:20,971
- All thanks to me, right?
- Yes. It's all thanks to you.

141
00:12:21,371 --> 00:12:24,171
You weren't nervous and did great.
You were a total pro.

142
00:12:25,741 --> 00:12:29,651
I hope Grandma saw everything okay.
I was so nervous.

143
00:12:29,711 --> 00:12:31,311
I couldn't even spot our family.

144
00:12:31,911 --> 00:12:33,751
Everyone had a great view
right from the front row.

145
00:12:34,051 --> 00:12:35,051
Really?

146
00:12:35,951 --> 00:12:37,821
It's finally over.

147
00:12:39,561 --> 00:12:40,561
Mom.

148
00:12:41,261 --> 00:12:42,261
Yes?

149
00:12:42,521 --> 00:12:43,691
What stage is it?

150
00:12:44,061 --> 00:12:45,731
Will you be okay
if you have the surgery?

151
00:12:51,201 --> 00:12:55,371
I took the call from the hospital
before the show started.

152
00:12:57,111 --> 00:13:00,411
It's okay. It's nothing
to worry too much about.

153
00:13:02,611 --> 00:13:04,211
Was I the only one who didn't know?

154
00:13:05,951 --> 00:13:09,591
Woo Jae doesn't know either.
I was going to tell you today.

155
00:13:10,221 --> 00:13:12,861
I didn't say anything because
I didn't want to ruin your show.

156
00:13:15,491 --> 00:13:19,161
Come on, don't look so sad.
You're the star today, okay?

157
00:13:22,201 --> 00:13:25,371
You did so well,
not letting on that you knew.

158
00:13:26,771 --> 00:13:29,871
- Are you sure you're okay?
- Of course.

159
00:13:32,041 --> 00:13:33,981
- Here we are. Where is she?
- Where are they?

160
00:13:33,981 --> 00:13:35,441
- Where are they?
- Oh, there she is.

161
00:13:35,441 --> 00:13:37,951
Your grandma's here.
Don't cry. Okay?

162
00:13:38,611 --> 00:13:40,181
- Mother!
- Seong Mi!

163
00:13:41,381 --> 00:13:44,591
- Mother!
- My gosh, you did amazing!

164
00:13:44,591 --> 00:13:46,261
Thank you.

165
00:13:47,161 --> 00:13:48,761
- Ju Ah.
- Honey, you were...

166
00:13:48,761 --> 00:13:51,331
absolutely the best.
You looked like a total pro. Oh, my.

167
00:13:51,391 --> 00:13:52,391
Thank you.

168
00:13:52,731 --> 00:13:56,271
- Seong Mi, you were amazing.
- Thank you.

169
00:13:56,431 --> 00:13:59,641
- Ju Ah, you were amazing too.
- She sure was.

170
00:13:59,701 --> 00:14:02,401
- Thanks, Uncle.
- Mom, you looked stunning.

171
00:14:02,471 --> 00:14:04,541
Thank you, sweetie.

172
00:14:05,671 --> 00:14:07,611
Ju Ah, you worked so hard.

173
00:14:07,711 --> 00:14:10,481
Thank you
for making my wish come true.

174
00:14:13,151 --> 00:14:17,021
I know, Mother. I was so happy
today, all thanks to Ju Ah.

175
00:14:17,091 --> 00:14:18,191
I know.

176
00:14:19,821 --> 00:14:22,691
But honey, are you okay?
Aren't you tired?

177
00:14:22,931 --> 00:14:27,031
- I am tired. Let's go home.
- Okay, let's get going, all right?

178
00:14:35,571 --> 00:14:40,141
The media is already full
of articles about you, sir.

179
00:14:40,341 --> 00:14:43,911
It brings me great joy to see you
looking so well, Mr. Chairman.

180
00:14:43,981 --> 00:14:45,081
As if!

181
00:14:49,251 --> 00:14:51,421
You still have your sense of humor.

182
00:14:51,551 --> 00:14:54,291
When did you get so petty?

183
00:14:54,621 --> 00:14:57,161
- Sir?
- The Fashion Division.

184
00:14:57,531 --> 00:15:00,401
Why are you so hell-bent
on destroying it?

185
00:15:00,561 --> 00:15:03,071
I'm not in my grave yet.

186
00:15:03,131 --> 00:15:05,601
Gosh, Mr. Chairman...

187
00:15:06,031 --> 00:15:10,371
This wasn't my decision alone.
It was all for the good of Taehan...

188
00:15:12,411 --> 00:15:15,981
Director Yang, is this how
you relayed our conversation?

189
00:15:16,411 --> 00:15:19,511
You were the one who came to me
asking for help, Director Yang.

190
00:15:20,581 --> 00:15:22,681
You're still as good
at making things up as ever.

191
00:15:23,791 --> 00:15:28,361
Stick to the original agreement.
Based on the fashion show's outcome,

192
00:15:28,521 --> 00:15:32,061
decide Director Yang's future
with the company. Fair and square.

193
00:15:42,801 --> 00:15:43,841
- Sir.
- Yes.

194
00:15:44,771 --> 00:15:46,611
Is it true that Hye Su
and Director Yang aren't a couple?

195
00:15:46,681 --> 00:15:47,711
Yes, sir. That's correct.

196
00:15:47,911 --> 00:15:50,781
Just in case, we need to remove him
before they fall for each other.

197
00:15:50,851 --> 00:15:52,511
Things get messy
when family gets involved.

198
00:15:52,911 --> 00:15:55,651
- Leak some bad press about him.
- What kind of...

199
00:15:55,721 --> 00:15:56,721
Find something.

200
00:15:58,791 --> 00:16:01,721
Dad, you finally regained
consciousness and showed up...

201
00:16:01,791 --> 00:16:03,961
just to pull this? Seriously!

202
00:16:05,061 --> 00:16:08,131
Director Yang has contributed
so much to the Fashion Division.

203
00:16:08,131 --> 00:16:12,331
You should've secured a longer deal,
regardless of the show's outcome.

204
00:16:12,331 --> 00:16:13,601
Gosh, honestly.

205
00:16:13,941 --> 00:16:16,141
Hey, are you serious right now?

206
00:16:16,611 --> 00:16:19,311
Using the Chairman for my fights,
what does that make me look like?

207
00:16:20,541 --> 00:16:21,541
You.

208
00:16:22,241 --> 00:16:23,711
Yes, Mr. Chairman.

209
00:16:23,981 --> 00:16:26,151
I only agreed to bring you on...

210
00:16:26,251 --> 00:16:28,321
because I thought
you'd marry Hye Su.

211
00:16:29,451 --> 00:16:30,651
Exactly.

212
00:16:31,091 --> 00:16:35,221
If you're not going to marry her,
at least work to repay her kindness.

213
00:16:35,661 --> 00:16:36,831
That's what I'm saying!

214
00:16:47,501 --> 00:16:48,501
Woo Jae.

215
00:16:49,101 --> 00:16:52,241
What's the exact diagnosis?
The size of the tumor?

216
00:16:53,041 --> 00:16:54,041
Any signs of metastasis?

217
00:16:54,611 --> 00:16:56,341
The tumor isn't large.

218
00:16:56,951 --> 00:17:00,451
And according to the tests,
it's a single lesion for now,

219
00:17:00,581 --> 00:17:02,951
so they think I'll be fine
with just surgery.

220
00:17:03,821 --> 00:17:04,821
What about chemo?

221
00:17:04,951 --> 00:17:08,391
They decided
they'll make a call on chemo...

222
00:17:08,591 --> 00:17:09,961
after the surgery,
based on the pathology report.

223
00:17:13,061 --> 00:17:14,561
My gosh.

224
00:17:14,901 --> 00:17:19,471
Leave it to a family of doctors.
It's like I'm in a medical drama!

225
00:17:20,771 --> 00:17:24,611
Mom, I can't believe you did
that fashion show in your condition.

226
00:17:25,071 --> 00:17:26,981
I wanted to do it.

227
00:17:27,481 --> 00:17:30,451
It might've been my last time
on that stage...

228
00:17:30,451 --> 00:17:31,911
What do you mean, "last?"

229
00:17:32,251 --> 00:17:35,321
- Don't say that. Why even say that?
- No, I just mean...

230
00:17:35,381 --> 00:17:37,091
Hey, come on.

231
00:17:38,951 --> 00:17:42,221
I pushed myself
to be on stage with Ju Ah.

232
00:17:43,631 --> 00:17:45,391
If you all fall apart,

233
00:17:45,761 --> 00:17:48,131
it'll be even harder on your mom.
You know that, right?

234
00:17:48,731 --> 00:17:50,471
And you, Grandma? Are you okay?

235
00:17:50,901 --> 00:17:52,201
I have to be.

236
00:17:52,571 --> 00:17:53,971
That's the only way
I can take care of your mom.

237
00:17:54,271 --> 00:17:55,271
Right.

238
00:17:55,671 --> 00:17:59,241
If the family is struggling,
the patient feels withdrawn too.

239
00:17:59,841 --> 00:18:02,681
It lowers their sense of autonomy
and self-efficacy.

240
00:18:03,281 --> 00:18:05,681
So just treat me like you always do.

241
00:18:06,381 --> 00:18:07,751
You understand
what I'm saying, right?

242
00:18:16,291 --> 00:18:18,961
Wait, what about the work dinner?
Why did you come home?

243
00:18:19,291 --> 00:18:23,301
Everyone worked so hard.
Today's to celebrate with your team.

244
00:18:23,701 --> 00:18:27,101
Mom, come on.
How can I be in the mood for that?

245
00:18:27,471 --> 00:18:29,741
- But still...
- It's fine.

246
00:18:29,741 --> 00:18:31,571
There will be other chances.

247
00:18:32,111 --> 00:18:33,681
I'm just saying it's a shame.

248
00:18:34,081 --> 00:18:37,081
If I weren't sick,
I'd be having a drink with you all.

249
00:18:37,681 --> 00:18:40,951
- Are you in a lot of pain?
- It's just an expression.

250
00:18:41,851 --> 00:18:43,321
So, why did you follow me in here?

251
00:18:43,651 --> 00:18:45,951
What? To apologize
for being mean to me...

252
00:18:45,951 --> 00:18:47,621
because you didn't know I was sick?

253
00:18:48,721 --> 00:18:50,261
Honestly...

254
00:18:50,731 --> 00:18:53,201
Let's see.
What did you have to apologize for?

255
00:18:54,631 --> 00:18:56,501
For nagging you
about gaining weight...

256
00:18:56,771 --> 00:18:58,401
and refusing to be your driver.

257
00:18:59,631 --> 00:19:00,941
So you do know what you did.

258
00:19:03,001 --> 00:19:04,241
Are you really okay?

259
00:19:05,311 --> 00:19:08,181
Yes. Now that the fashion show
has wrapped up successfully,

260
00:19:08,381 --> 00:19:10,381
I feel much more relieved
and at ease.

261
00:19:11,481 --> 00:19:12,551
Good.

262
00:19:13,321 --> 00:19:16,221
Please thank the Vice President
and Director Yang for me.

263
00:19:17,121 --> 00:19:20,791
Director Yang has been helping me
this whole time without you knowing.

264
00:19:21,291 --> 00:19:23,691
Right.

265
00:19:36,171 --> 00:19:37,571
About us dating...

266
00:19:38,171 --> 00:19:42,811
- Let's keep it secret for a while.
- Why? Having second thoughts now?

267
00:19:43,381 --> 00:19:45,181
You're stressed out
with all the prep work,

268
00:19:45,351 --> 00:19:47,751
and Dr. Han seems to be
under a lot of stress too.

269
00:19:49,221 --> 00:19:50,951
How about after the fashion show?

270
00:19:52,721 --> 00:19:54,321
So that's why he said that.

271
00:20:06,431 --> 00:20:09,071
Hey.
Are you still at the team dinner?

272
00:20:09,571 --> 00:20:12,271
No, we wrapped up a while ago.
I'm back at my apartment.

273
00:20:13,011 --> 00:20:15,481
I see. You know...

274
00:20:15,681 --> 00:20:19,011
I heard you found out
that Dr. Han is sick.

275
00:20:19,681 --> 00:20:20,681
I did.

276
00:20:21,581 --> 00:20:25,221
Thank you for taking care of my mom
without me knowing.

277
00:20:26,661 --> 00:20:29,761
Are you mad I didn't tell you?

278
00:20:30,591 --> 00:20:34,231
Why would I be mad?
I understand your reasons.

279
00:20:35,401 --> 00:20:38,431
Right.
Now that the fashion show's over,

280
00:20:39,101 --> 00:20:40,771
just focus on Dr. Han's treatment.

281
00:20:41,501 --> 00:20:43,311
Her surgery is on Monday, right?

282
00:20:44,441 --> 00:20:46,041
You know more about it than I do.

283
00:20:47,011 --> 00:20:48,581
Hey, no more secrets between us now,
for real.

284
00:20:49,381 --> 00:20:53,521
What are you talking about?
You agreed to quit for the budget.

285
00:20:55,381 --> 00:20:57,951
Gosh, why on earth did Director Baek
have to bring that up?

286
00:20:58,321 --> 00:21:00,091
Don't change the subject.

287
00:21:00,661 --> 00:21:03,091
So, what happened?
The Chairman was there, too.

288
00:21:03,891 --> 00:21:08,701
For now, the decision will depend
on the fashion show's performance.

289
00:21:10,271 --> 00:21:11,571
That's a relief, at least.

290
00:21:13,301 --> 00:21:15,741
Well, you know...

291
00:21:16,741 --> 00:21:17,741
Yes?

292
00:21:21,441 --> 00:21:22,441
What is it?

293
00:21:24,611 --> 00:21:25,611
Never mind.

294
00:21:26,311 --> 00:21:27,521
I'll see you at the office.

295
00:21:29,481 --> 00:21:30,491
All right.

296
00:21:36,521 --> 00:21:39,891
Are you on the phone all night?
Let's have a drink!

297
00:21:42,231 --> 00:21:43,971
"Let's have a drink?"

298
00:21:44,901 --> 00:21:47,471
Isn't that the formal way to say it?

299
00:21:47,741 --> 00:21:48,771
I guess not?

300
00:21:49,801 --> 00:21:52,911
Hey, I can talk casually to myself,
can't I?

301
00:21:53,641 --> 00:21:56,441
So being drunk is your excuse
to say whatever you want, right?

302
00:21:56,951 --> 00:22:00,421
No, I'm just...
I'm in a very good mood, that's all.

303
00:22:01,621 --> 00:22:03,691
Yes? And what are you
so happy about?

304
00:22:04,051 --> 00:22:07,161
It was me who saved you, Director.

305
00:22:07,291 --> 00:22:09,061
- Excuse me?
- Oh, come on.

306
00:22:09,521 --> 00:22:14,301
To stop Director Baek's plan
to oust you,

307
00:22:14,901 --> 00:22:17,001
I was the one
who went and convinced...

308
00:22:17,201 --> 00:22:21,101
the VP to bring the Chairman
to the show. That's right, me!

309
00:22:21,901 --> 00:22:26,541
Without that, the show's results
wouldn't have mattered, Director.

310
00:22:26,881 --> 00:22:28,511
You would've just been fired.
You know that?

311
00:22:32,411 --> 00:22:34,081
Man. Seriously.

312
00:22:34,951 --> 00:22:39,521
Man... Why do you look like you have
the weight of the world on you?

313
00:22:39,721 --> 00:22:42,221
Hey, seriously.
Why are you acting like this?

314
00:22:43,991 --> 00:22:47,161
Come on, don't worry so much. Okay?

315
00:22:47,831 --> 00:22:51,831
Dr. Han Seong Mi's surgery
is going to be fine. Right?

316
00:22:53,441 --> 00:22:55,841
Once she recovers,

317
00:22:56,141 --> 00:22:59,471
you need to tell them about you two.
Got it?

318
00:23:01,341 --> 00:23:03,311
Hey, why aren't you answering?

319
00:23:04,351 --> 00:23:07,381
To be honest, I'm still debating it.

320
00:23:08,051 --> 00:23:09,521
What? What is there to debate?

321
00:23:09,981 --> 00:23:13,251
I'll tell you what I'm debating
once I've made up my mind.

322
00:23:13,491 --> 00:23:15,191
What? What does that even mean?

323
00:23:15,891 --> 00:23:16,991
What does what mean?

324
00:23:18,661 --> 00:23:21,361
And there you go again,
dropping the formalities.

325
00:23:22,201 --> 00:23:25,401
Oh, man... Are my ears working?

326
00:23:26,131 --> 00:23:28,171
I'm going to take a leak.

327
00:23:29,301 --> 00:23:31,711
- I need to pee.
- "Pee?"

328
00:23:32,411 --> 00:23:33,411
What was that about?

329
00:23:40,011 --> 00:23:41,021
Yes, Mother.

330
00:23:41,421 --> 00:23:43,451
Can you come to the house tomorrow?

331
00:23:43,721 --> 00:23:44,991
There's something I want
to talk to you about.

332
00:23:45,691 --> 00:23:46,691
Tomorrow?

333
00:23:49,261 --> 00:23:51,261
Okay, I get it.
I'll see you tomorrow.

334
00:23:55,001 --> 00:23:56,731
So, is Hyun Bin coming over?

335
00:23:56,901 --> 00:23:59,171
Yes. But he said he wants to meet
somewhere else.

336
00:23:59,731 --> 00:24:00,871
Do you want to come along?

337
00:24:01,801 --> 00:24:05,711
- I can't. I have plans tomorrow.
- Really?

338
00:24:06,841 --> 00:24:08,311
Hey, honey.

339
00:24:08,911 --> 00:24:12,081
- My throat's a little scratchy.
- Really?

340
00:24:12,381 --> 00:24:15,981
- Should I get you some warm water?
- That would be great, thanks.

341
00:24:16,521 --> 00:24:17,521
Okay.

342
00:24:25,261 --> 00:24:27,231
(Kang Hyeon Cheol, 51 Taegyeong-ro,
Onjeong-gu, Onjeong City)

343
00:24:30,731 --> 00:24:33,431
Post-traumatic pain,
suspected fracture.

344
00:24:33,501 --> 00:24:34,701
(Korean Medicine Doctor
Yang Dong Ik)

345
00:24:34,771 --> 00:24:35,771
Kang Hyeon Cheol?

346
00:25:05,771 --> 00:25:09,571
(Ms. Jo Hyeon Suk)

347
00:25:39,001 --> 00:25:41,171
Have you been following me
this whole time?

348
00:25:42,901 --> 00:25:44,741
Are you some kind of pervert?

349
00:25:45,141 --> 00:25:47,411
I've been trying to ignore
my feelings and avoid you,

350
00:25:48,341 --> 00:25:50,711
but I can't hide my feelings
any longer.

351
00:25:56,621 --> 00:25:58,691
No matter what happens,
we won't be shaken.

352
00:25:59,321 --> 00:26:00,391
Promise.

353
00:26:02,721 --> 00:26:03,731
Promise.

354
00:26:07,501 --> 00:26:09,561
I can't live without you now.

355
00:26:16,171 --> 00:26:17,171
Happy?

356
00:26:18,311 --> 00:26:19,541
I love this.

357
00:26:21,181 --> 00:26:22,341
Go faster!

358
00:27:32,111 --> 00:27:34,781
Yes, Vice President.
I just arrived at the hospital.

359
00:27:35,181 --> 00:27:37,991
The caregiver is running a bit late,
so just come on up to the room.

360
00:27:38,791 --> 00:27:40,391
What? You mean me?

361
00:27:50,531 --> 00:27:53,001
The caregiver's in the elevator,
so let's head out.

362
00:27:56,171 --> 00:27:58,511
He seemed fine yesterday.

363
00:27:58,871 --> 00:28:01,411
Tell me about it.
He's been in and out of it.

364
00:28:02,211 --> 00:28:04,551
So I guess yesterday
he was "in" it, thankfully?

365
00:28:05,281 --> 00:28:07,351
Right. And today he's "out."

366
00:28:13,121 --> 00:28:14,161
Wait...

367
00:28:16,091 --> 00:28:17,531
I think he's staring at this.

368
00:28:18,131 --> 00:28:20,361
- What's that?
- This?

369
00:28:22,931 --> 00:28:23,931
A chewy cookie.

370
00:28:24,201 --> 00:28:27,341
No. Dad can't eat things like this.
Let's go.

371
00:28:27,641 --> 00:28:28,641
But...

372
00:28:35,081 --> 00:28:37,411
- Let's go.
- Right. I think something...

373
00:28:38,051 --> 00:28:40,521
fell on the floor. Coming.

374
00:28:57,131 --> 00:28:59,901
The reason
the Chairman was glaring at me...

375
00:29:00,231 --> 00:29:02,741
It couldn't be
because he thinks I'm your...

376
00:29:02,971 --> 00:29:05,341
boyfriend, could it?

377
00:29:07,281 --> 00:29:08,781
He was looking at your face,
Mr. Park.

378
00:29:10,711 --> 00:29:11,951
My face? Why?

379
00:29:13,081 --> 00:29:16,721
A lot of crazy things have happened
since my dad was hospitalized.

380
00:29:17,591 --> 00:29:21,391
We've had total strangers show up
at the hospital claiming to be...

381
00:29:21,461 --> 00:29:22,791
my half-siblings or something.

382
00:29:23,521 --> 00:29:26,091
What? Seriously?
What a bunch of scammers.

383
00:29:26,091 --> 00:29:29,461
But the crazy part is,
my dad doesn't deny it.

384
00:29:30,701 --> 00:29:33,841
He just stares at them and says
he'll order a DNA test.

385
00:29:33,941 --> 00:29:35,401
What do you think that means?

386
00:29:36,641 --> 00:29:38,971
Wait, so you think he might actually
have another kid out there?

387
00:29:39,071 --> 00:29:40,881
That's what I'm saying.

388
00:29:41,941 --> 00:29:43,581
But the real one
still hasn't shown up.

389
00:29:44,781 --> 00:29:47,451
Maybe the person in question
doesn't even know.

390
00:29:48,521 --> 00:29:49,621
That's possible.

391
00:29:50,221 --> 00:29:51,351
Still, though...

392
00:29:51,921 --> 00:29:54,921
Finding out you're a long-lost heir
to a fortune...

393
00:29:55,721 --> 00:29:57,091
That would be a rush.

394
00:29:57,161 --> 00:30:00,191
I wish one would show up.
It'd be nice to have some backup.

395
00:30:00,261 --> 00:30:04,471
Be careful what you wish for.
You could end up losing everything.

396
00:30:05,501 --> 00:30:06,501
You think so?

397
00:30:11,411 --> 00:30:12,971
This is delicious.

398
00:30:13,841 --> 00:30:14,841
It's good, right?

399
00:30:19,211 --> 00:30:21,521
You've been so busy lately.
What a surprise to see you home.

400
00:30:22,051 --> 00:30:25,291
Come on, you're admitted tomorrow.
How could I be anywhere else?

401
00:30:25,951 --> 00:30:28,661
- I'm telling you, I'm fine.
- But...

402
00:30:28,991 --> 00:30:30,931
Are you really not scared?

403
00:30:31,291 --> 00:30:35,031
Of course not.
I was nervous waiting for results,

404
00:30:35,101 --> 00:30:38,231
but now that I know what's going on,
I actually feel relieved.

405
00:30:38,401 --> 00:30:40,971
Hey. Are you packed
for the hospital?

406
00:30:40,971 --> 00:30:44,811
- Yes.
- Wait, where are you two going?

407
00:30:46,111 --> 00:30:48,041
I'm taking her out for a nice meal.

408
00:30:48,111 --> 00:30:52,351
Good. The fast starts tomorrow.
That's a great idea.

409
00:30:52,681 --> 00:30:54,481
You should've done this sooner.

410
00:30:54,651 --> 00:30:56,881
I know.
I feel bad it's so last-minute.

411
00:30:58,091 --> 00:30:59,621
You should come with us, too.

412
00:30:59,621 --> 00:31:03,791
No, it's okay. You two
should enjoy your time alone.

413
00:31:03,961 --> 00:31:05,831
- We'll get going then.
- Okay.

414
00:31:05,891 --> 00:31:08,531
- We'll be back.
- Okay, have fun.

415
00:31:15,271 --> 00:31:19,311
Is something wrong at the office?

416
00:31:19,771 --> 00:31:20,781
No, it's nothing.

417
00:31:20,841 --> 00:31:24,251
Then why do you suddenly want
to go back to Argentina?

418
00:31:24,781 --> 00:31:28,921
Are things not working out
with the person you're seeing?

419
00:31:30,021 --> 00:31:31,021
That's not it.

420
00:31:31,751 --> 00:31:33,961
By the way,
how do you like running the store?

421
00:31:34,691 --> 00:31:38,161
It's fun. But come on,
don't change the subject.

422
00:31:38,231 --> 00:31:40,131
I came here today dead set
on getting an answer.

423
00:31:43,331 --> 00:31:44,771
Saved by the bell.

424
00:31:45,571 --> 00:31:46,571
Hello?

425
00:31:48,741 --> 00:31:49,741
Yes.

426
00:31:51,371 --> 00:31:52,741
An article about Dr. Han?

427
00:31:53,811 --> 00:31:55,511
No, I haven't seen it yet.

428
00:31:56,241 --> 00:31:57,241
What?

429
00:31:58,851 --> 00:32:02,751
Wait,
who would leak that information?

430
00:32:05,921 --> 00:32:09,391
Make sure no information
about the hospital gets out.

431
00:32:09,821 --> 00:32:11,491
Step up monitoring...

432
00:32:11,891 --> 00:32:14,661
to respond quickly
to any speculative reports.

433
00:32:14,801 --> 00:32:15,801
Understood.

434
00:32:17,671 --> 00:32:20,871
Hyun Bin,
does Dr. Han have breast cancer?

435
00:32:24,241 --> 00:32:28,511
"Taking a break from all TV shows."
Gosh, this is awful.

436
00:32:33,711 --> 00:32:34,751
Should we sit over there?

437
00:32:38,851 --> 00:32:39,891
Really?

438
00:32:42,921 --> 00:32:43,921
My goodness...

439
00:32:47,131 --> 00:32:48,301
Oh, my gosh.

440
00:32:50,331 --> 00:32:51,371
Dr. Han.

441
00:32:52,171 --> 00:32:54,371
My gosh. Fancy seeing you here.

442
00:32:56,641 --> 00:32:58,841
- Hello.
- Hi.

443
00:32:59,111 --> 00:33:02,911
Doctor, is it okay for you
to be out and about like this?

444
00:33:03,611 --> 00:33:04,681
Excuse me?

445
00:33:05,611 --> 00:33:07,651
They're saying
you have breast cancer.

446
00:33:09,181 --> 00:33:10,851
About that...

447
00:33:11,151 --> 00:33:13,521
An article was just posted online.

448
00:33:13,721 --> 00:33:15,621
- What? An article?
- An article?

449
00:33:15,621 --> 00:33:19,631
Yes. I'll do everything I can
to minimize the damage.

450
00:33:22,131 --> 00:33:23,131
What's going on?

451
00:33:23,401 --> 00:33:27,231
So, Hyun Bin, you knew
Dr. Han was sick this whole time?

452
00:33:28,171 --> 00:33:30,911
Is that why you were
driving her around?

453
00:33:32,211 --> 00:33:35,111
Gosh, you should've just told me.

454
00:33:36,311 --> 00:33:40,611
I really put my foot in my mouth.
I'm so sorry, Doctor.

455
00:33:41,121 --> 00:33:42,451
It's all right.

456
00:33:42,821 --> 00:33:47,221
- Well then.
- Wait. So... How serious is it?

457
00:33:47,291 --> 00:33:49,161
You'll be okay after the surgery,
right?

458
00:33:49,661 --> 00:33:53,191
- Yes, she'll be fine.
- Oh, my goodness.

459
00:33:53,261 --> 00:33:54,661
Mother.

460
00:33:57,471 --> 00:33:58,931
Well...

461
00:33:59,901 --> 00:34:02,241
I hope you have a speedy recovery,
Doctor.

462
00:34:02,841 --> 00:34:06,871
Yes, thank you. Enjoy your meal.

463
00:34:07,611 --> 00:34:10,081
I'll see you at work then.

464
00:34:10,341 --> 00:34:11,351
Yes.

465
00:34:16,851 --> 00:34:19,351
Mom, should we just leave?

466
00:34:19,591 --> 00:34:23,391
- Yes, let's go somewhere else.
- Okay.

467
00:34:23,761 --> 00:34:27,131
That woman... Didn't she seem happy
that I have cancer?

468
00:34:28,031 --> 00:34:29,761
I doubt that.

469
00:34:31,331 --> 00:34:32,331
Let's go.

470
00:34:41,881 --> 00:34:43,081
But...

471
00:34:44,111 --> 00:34:47,251
I heard Dr. Han's parents
died young.

472
00:34:47,481 --> 00:34:49,351
I wonder if it's hereditary
or something.

473
00:34:49,681 --> 00:34:52,951
- What?
- Ms. Gong needs a checkup, too.

474
00:34:53,091 --> 00:34:56,261
They say lots of young people
get cancer these days.

475
00:34:58,331 --> 00:34:59,761
That's just awful.

476
00:35:02,461 --> 00:35:04,171
This is just unbelievable.

477
00:35:04,801 --> 00:35:08,401
Thank goodness the article came out
after the fashion show.

478
00:35:12,111 --> 00:35:14,711
- Hey, why are you back so soon?
- Hey.

479
00:35:15,081 --> 00:35:18,181
That article came out of nowhere.
I completely lost my appetite.

480
00:35:18,911 --> 00:35:19,911
You saw it, didn't you?

481
00:35:20,411 --> 00:35:23,521
I know. I guess
since you're so well-known,

482
00:35:23,621 --> 00:35:25,451
they'll make an article
out of anything.

483
00:35:25,691 --> 00:35:30,521
To top it off, we saw Bucket's wife
and Director Yang at the restaurant.

484
00:35:30,721 --> 00:35:31,731
What?

485
00:35:32,931 --> 00:35:34,861
We just happened to run into them.

486
00:35:35,461 --> 00:35:38,131
So? What?
What did Bucket's wife say to you?

487
00:35:38,501 --> 00:35:40,871
In a crowded restaurant,

488
00:35:40,971 --> 00:35:43,541
she asked, "You have breast cancer?"
Just like that.

489
00:35:43,601 --> 00:35:46,011
I swear, that family is just...
Gosh, seriously.

490
00:35:46,211 --> 00:35:50,141
Maybe I'm just paranoid,
but her concern didn't seem genuine.

491
00:35:50,211 --> 00:35:53,511
It really upset me, so we just left.

492
00:35:54,821 --> 00:35:57,381
Sweetie, let's just pretend we ate.

493
00:35:58,221 --> 00:36:01,521
Hey, come over here.
I'll make you something to eat.

494
00:36:01,521 --> 00:36:03,221
- Come on.
- Oh, really?

495
00:36:03,961 --> 00:36:05,461
Are you going to make something
from your recipe book?

496
00:36:05,531 --> 00:36:09,261
- Of course. You've eaten nothing.
- I told you, I'm fine.

497
00:36:16,501 --> 00:36:19,111
I didn't plan for them
to run into each other,

498
00:36:19,411 --> 00:36:20,941
not when Mom's so sick.

499
00:36:21,011 --> 00:36:22,981
How could I possibly do something
like that?

500
00:36:25,081 --> 00:36:26,981
I didn't say a word.

501
00:36:28,981 --> 00:36:30,051
I'm...

502
00:36:30,381 --> 00:36:32,491
going to break up
with Director Yang.

503
00:36:34,821 --> 00:36:35,821
I heard.

504
00:36:36,861 --> 00:36:37,861
What?

505
00:36:38,361 --> 00:36:40,461
That he was going to break up
with you.

506
00:36:41,101 --> 00:36:43,101
Director Yang came
and told me himself.

507
00:36:45,401 --> 00:36:47,071
I see.

508
00:36:50,871 --> 00:36:52,711
Are you really going to be okay?

509
00:36:54,841 --> 00:36:58,881
Of course, Grandma.
It's not a big deal.

510
00:36:59,011 --> 00:37:01,951
Office romances end all the time.

511
00:37:02,251 --> 00:37:05,021
Besides, with my mom being so sick,

512
00:37:05,091 --> 00:37:09,321
now's not the time for dating
the son of her worst enemy.

513
00:37:09,521 --> 00:37:10,521
Right?

514
00:37:12,431 --> 00:37:16,931
So please, don't you worry.
Mom will never find out.

515
00:37:19,201 --> 00:37:22,171
Man, I'm hungry.
I should get some of Dad's cooking.

516
00:37:24,671 --> 00:37:25,671
All right.

517
00:37:35,981 --> 00:37:37,691
Hello? Honey, where are you?

518
00:37:38,091 --> 00:37:39,091
Hey.

519
00:37:39,521 --> 00:37:41,261
I still have a few things
to take care of.

520
00:37:42,391 --> 00:37:43,391
What about you?

521
00:37:44,121 --> 00:37:46,691
I met up with Hyun Bin
and just got home.

522
00:37:47,291 --> 00:37:48,661
Okay, got it.

523
00:37:49,361 --> 00:37:50,801
We'll talk when I get home.

524
00:38:01,081 --> 00:38:02,511
(Kang Hyeon Cheol)

525
00:38:02,581 --> 00:38:03,781
(Shinna Snack Bar, Delivery Driver)

526
00:38:04,711 --> 00:38:08,721
She must not find out
that he's being tailed.

527
00:38:11,321 --> 00:38:12,321
Just...

528
00:38:13,151 --> 00:38:15,521
confirm what her relationship is
with that man.

529
00:38:16,791 --> 00:38:18,391
Yes, understood.

530
00:38:22,031 --> 00:38:24,101
(Kang Hyeon Cheol,
Shinna Snack Bar, Delivery Driver)

531
00:38:27,371 --> 00:38:29,501
It's the weekend.
What's got you so busy?

532
00:38:30,601 --> 00:38:33,911
I'm writing some English phrases
to use at the store.

533
00:38:34,141 --> 00:38:36,611
- For Mom?
- Yes.

534
00:38:37,141 --> 00:38:39,511
Since I'm leaving for the US
sooner than I expected,

535
00:38:39,611 --> 00:38:41,851
I won't be able to help her study
as much as I'd like.

536
00:38:41,921 --> 00:38:45,751
- So I wanted to give her this.
- I wish my English were better too.

537
00:38:47,021 --> 00:38:49,421
You have to come visit me, okay?

538
00:38:50,161 --> 00:38:53,591
- What's your English name?
- Veronica.

539
00:38:55,161 --> 00:38:58,231
- I'd better be careful.
- What? Why?

540
00:38:58,301 --> 00:39:01,971
My mom will recognize it.
It's the baptismal name she gave me.

541
00:39:02,771 --> 00:39:06,371
- Wow, you'd better be careful.
- Yes.

542
00:39:07,711 --> 00:39:09,811
(Dr. Han Seong Mi
Temporarily Halts Work for Health)

543
00:39:21,621 --> 00:39:23,221
You're all mine.

544
00:39:25,891 --> 00:39:28,831
Hey, if you're having a hard time,
always think of me.

545
00:39:30,101 --> 00:39:33,031
Yes. Things are tough,
and I am thinking of you.

546
00:39:43,611 --> 00:39:46,111
Why don't you two just hang out?
Why do you keep pulling me in?

547
00:39:46,351 --> 00:39:47,711
What?
Aren't I the one crashing the party?

548
00:39:48,721 --> 00:39:52,921
Crashing? One, two, three!
It takes three to make a party.

549
00:39:53,791 --> 00:39:56,261
Gosh, I have to study.
My midterms are coming up soon.

550
00:39:56,991 --> 00:40:01,031
Come on, you know the drill.
It's quality, not quantity.

551
00:40:01,601 --> 00:40:05,931
You should clear your head sometimes
for your focus to shoot up.

552
00:40:06,001 --> 00:40:07,001
Right?

553
00:40:07,841 --> 00:40:10,741
- He has a good point. Right, Ji Hu?
- Gosh, whatever.

554
00:40:11,471 --> 00:40:13,911
If I fail to take over the clinic,
it's on you, Mr. Gong.

555
00:40:14,371 --> 00:40:15,381
It's my responsibility?

556
00:40:15,681 --> 00:40:17,211
I happen to love
taking responsibility.

557
00:40:18,051 --> 00:40:19,111
Oh, man...

558
00:40:20,781 --> 00:40:23,881
- What?
- We should grab dinner sometime.

559
00:40:25,821 --> 00:40:27,791
- Hello.
- Hi, everyone.

560
00:40:31,061 --> 00:40:32,591
Well, what's this? You two together?

561
00:40:33,861 --> 00:40:36,801
- Are they finally going out?
- Yes.

562
00:40:37,101 --> 00:40:38,971
Success. Call me Cupid.

563
00:40:41,471 --> 00:40:44,871
So I guess this is your first date?

564
00:40:45,271 --> 00:40:48,381
Yes, we were just on our way
to see a movie.

565
00:40:48,541 --> 00:40:50,481
So, where are you three headed?

566
00:40:51,081 --> 00:40:53,851
We were going to shoot some hoops
at the park up ahead.

567
00:40:53,951 --> 00:40:55,981
Really? Hey, I love basketball.

568
00:40:56,521 --> 00:40:58,521
- Want to play a game with us?
- Yes!

569
00:41:00,421 --> 00:41:03,391
Hey, what are you doing?
They're on a date.

570
00:41:04,191 --> 00:41:06,391
Sorry.
Did I totally misread the room?

571
00:41:06,461 --> 00:41:08,961
No, not at all. It'll be more fun
if we play together.

572
00:41:09,601 --> 00:41:10,601
You're okay with that.
Right, Jin Ah?

573
00:41:11,201 --> 00:41:13,031
Yes, sure.

574
00:41:13,671 --> 00:41:14,671
It's fine.

575
00:41:14,941 --> 00:41:16,371
You're good with it?

576
00:41:17,401 --> 00:41:18,411
Okay!

577
00:41:26,251 --> 00:41:28,051
Yes!

578
00:41:29,581 --> 00:41:31,591
Pass it! Ji Hu, here!

579
00:41:32,991 --> 00:41:34,121
He's not afraid to foul, is he?

580
00:41:35,421 --> 00:41:39,931
I can't with them. Sorry,
you couldn't go to the movies.

581
00:41:40,631 --> 00:41:41,631
It's okay.

582
00:41:41,961 --> 00:41:44,161
Plus, I get to see Officer Jung
being all athletic.

583
00:41:44,571 --> 00:41:45,571
So I'm not complaining.

584
00:41:45,871 --> 00:41:48,371
You two look really good together,
by the way.

585
00:41:48,701 --> 00:41:50,101
It's sweet to see a new couple.

586
00:41:50,671 --> 00:41:51,671
Thank you.

587
00:41:52,511 --> 00:41:55,111
You must have a lot on your minds,
though.

588
00:41:55,811 --> 00:41:56,811
Yes, we do.

589
00:41:57,141 --> 00:42:00,011
It's hard enough with the doctors
not on speaking terms,

590
00:42:00,581 --> 00:42:02,121
and now Dr. Han is sick
on top of it all.

591
00:42:02,551 --> 00:42:04,321
It must make it even harder
to tell both of your families.

592
00:42:05,451 --> 00:42:08,321
Until she gets through her treatment
and recovers,

593
00:42:08,661 --> 00:42:10,321
we'll just have to be careful
not to get caught.

594
00:42:10,861 --> 00:42:13,391
We'll run interference for you
until then.

595
00:42:13,831 --> 00:42:14,831
Hush!

596
00:42:15,531 --> 00:42:16,531
Thanks.

597
00:42:25,841 --> 00:42:26,841
Here you go.

598
00:42:28,181 --> 00:42:31,751
I wrote down phrases you might need
for your foreign customers.

599
00:42:32,111 --> 00:42:35,981
So even after I leave for the US,
promise you'll practice every day.

600
00:42:37,681 --> 00:42:40,791
I will. Thank you.

601
00:42:42,321 --> 00:42:44,291
Make sure
you get your certification.

602
00:42:44,831 --> 00:42:49,531
If there's anything you want to try,
just go for it and don't hesitate.

603
00:42:50,701 --> 00:42:52,931
- I will.
- And...

604
00:42:56,641 --> 00:42:59,911
You have to come visit me
in Baltimore, too.

605
00:43:01,211 --> 00:43:04,541
Of course. And Min Seo,
you come visit Korea again, too.

606
00:43:04,981 --> 00:43:05,981
Yes.

607
00:43:05,981 --> 00:43:10,521
When you come, don't stay elsewhere.
You have to stay with us, got it?

608
00:43:11,181 --> 00:43:12,191
Yes, Mother.

609
00:43:13,791 --> 00:43:15,591
- What?
- I'm home.

610
00:43:17,191 --> 00:43:19,661
Honey, what took you so long?

611
00:43:20,061 --> 00:43:22,861
I had a continuing education seminar
at the medical association.

612
00:43:23,231 --> 00:43:27,301
- Hurry and get changed for dinner.
- Okay.

613
00:43:27,431 --> 00:43:29,741
- Min Seo, can you give me a hand?
- Sure.

614
00:43:35,481 --> 00:43:36,981
By the way, Father.

615
00:43:37,381 --> 00:43:40,111
I tried talking Hyun Bin
out of leaving.

616
00:43:40,451 --> 00:43:42,451
But I don't think
he's going to change his mind.

617
00:43:43,721 --> 00:43:44,891
When is he leaving?

618
00:43:45,451 --> 00:43:48,991
I'm not exactly sure,
but it won't be right away.

619
00:43:49,491 --> 00:43:52,091
Let's spend quality time
with Hyun Bin before he leaves.

620
00:43:52,561 --> 00:43:54,191
This must be the hardest on you.

621
00:43:55,201 --> 00:43:56,231
Even if he does go,

622
00:43:56,561 --> 00:43:58,531
I plan on looking after him
and checking in on him even more.

623
00:43:58,901 --> 00:44:00,071
Good, you do that.

624
00:44:01,341 --> 00:44:05,241
Anyway, I've felt awful
since hearing of Dr. Han Seong Mi.

625
00:44:05,511 --> 00:44:08,381
I know, right?
It's bad enough that she's sick,

626
00:44:08,541 --> 00:44:10,081
but then an article had to come out
about it.

627
00:44:10,781 --> 00:44:11,781
You didn't know either?

628
00:44:12,051 --> 00:44:13,351
What? No, I didn't.

629
00:44:14,251 --> 00:44:15,521
I found out from that article.

630
00:44:16,051 --> 00:44:19,921
Still, breast cancer is very curable
if it's caught early.

631
00:44:20,691 --> 00:44:22,691
- Really?
- Yes.

632
00:44:22,761 --> 00:44:26,091
But she's still in her prime.
It's just terrible.

633
00:44:26,361 --> 00:44:30,061
I saw her with her daughter earlier
while I was eating with Hyun Bin,

634
00:44:30,431 --> 00:44:32,631
and it was just heartbreaking.

635
00:44:33,471 --> 00:44:35,571
Dr. Gong seems unwell lately too,
doesn't he?

636
00:44:36,501 --> 00:44:38,911
What? Well...

637
00:44:39,611 --> 00:44:42,141
I guess Jeong Han's running around
to get on TV...

638
00:44:42,811 --> 00:44:44,141
must have all been for Seong Mi.

639
00:44:49,681 --> 00:44:53,821
Is it because this is my last meal?
Everything tastes so delicious.

640
00:44:56,691 --> 00:44:58,961
Here, have some
seasoned broccoli, too.

641
00:44:59,231 --> 00:45:02,431
It's high in sulforaphane,
so it's good for fighting cancer.

642
00:45:03,531 --> 00:45:07,001
Looks like Jeong Han's an expert now
on anti-cancer diets.

643
00:45:07,731 --> 00:45:11,641
Tell me about it.
He's been doting on me a lot lately.

644
00:45:11,811 --> 00:45:14,881
- Being sick is almost worth it.
- Honestly...

645
00:45:14,941 --> 00:45:16,711
- Mom, don't say that!
- Don't say that!

646
00:45:16,711 --> 00:45:19,251
Focus on surgery
and recovering fast.

647
00:45:19,251 --> 00:45:22,881
- My point, exactly.
- Okay, all right. Tough crowd.

648
00:45:24,521 --> 00:45:27,651
So, when you get admitted tomorrow,

649
00:45:28,361 --> 00:45:29,361
who's going with you?

650
00:45:29,761 --> 00:45:32,231
What do you mean?
I'm her mother. Of course, I'll go.

651
00:45:32,761 --> 00:45:34,761
I'm the eldest daughter,
so I should be the one to go.

652
00:45:35,231 --> 00:45:37,531
I already took the day off.
I'm her one and only son.

653
00:45:37,601 --> 00:45:41,371
No. All of you, quiet down!
I'm going.

654
00:45:41,471 --> 00:45:43,771
I'm her husband,
and I'm her guardian, okay?

655
00:45:44,171 --> 00:45:45,171
Right, honey?

656
00:45:45,471 --> 00:45:46,471
Well, what's gotten into you?

657
00:45:47,671 --> 00:45:51,041
Seong Mi, why can't we all go?
We're family.

658
00:45:52,411 --> 00:45:55,621
Because I don't want to.
I just need one guardian.

659
00:45:55,681 --> 00:45:57,521
- Fine, I'll go then.
- Exactly.

660
00:45:57,581 --> 00:45:59,651
- I'll go.
- Hey, wait! Then let's do this.

661
00:46:00,451 --> 00:46:03,491
- Rock, paper, scissors. One round.
- What? That's ridiculous.

662
00:46:03,491 --> 00:46:04,591
With rock, paper, scissors?

663
00:46:04,661 --> 00:46:07,261
Fine. This is ridiculous, but fine,
let's just do rock, paper, scissors.

664
00:46:07,391 --> 00:46:09,401
So this is it? One round settles it?

665
00:46:09,701 --> 00:46:10,861
Okay, perfect. Let's go.

666
00:46:11,231 --> 00:46:13,301
Obviously, I'm going to win.
This is so silly. Gosh, honestly.

667
00:46:13,371 --> 00:46:17,201
Honestly, what's the fuss about?
Am I going on a trip abroad or what?

668
00:46:17,441 --> 00:46:18,441
Don't worry. I'll win.

669
00:46:18,511 --> 00:46:21,371
Hold on. Seong Mi, stay out of this.

670
00:46:21,371 --> 00:46:23,081
All right, is everyone ready?
Here we go, rock-paper-scissors.

671
00:46:23,081 --> 00:46:24,141
- Yes, all right.
- Okay, ready.

672
00:46:24,181 --> 00:46:26,711
- Bring it on.
- Ready, set, rock-paper-scissors!

673
00:46:27,581 --> 00:46:29,781
No, wait a minute. Mom didn't play.

674
00:46:29,851 --> 00:46:31,321
- That's right. Mom, you must play.
- What about Dad?

675
00:46:31,381 --> 00:46:32,391
I told you I'd go.

676
00:46:32,451 --> 00:46:34,821
- No!
- No, me! I'm going.

677
00:46:34,891 --> 00:46:37,521
- Fine, let's do it.
- Ready, set, rock-paper-scissors!

678
00:46:37,821 --> 00:46:40,131
- Yes! You're out!
- Dad's out!

679
00:46:40,191 --> 00:46:42,131
- No way! The loser goes.
- No, that's not it.

680
00:46:42,201 --> 00:46:43,631
- The loser...
- Next.

681
00:46:43,631 --> 00:46:45,071
You should've treated her better.

682
00:46:45,131 --> 00:46:47,531
Okay, next round!
Rock-paper-scissors!

683
00:46:47,731 --> 00:46:51,671
- Okay! Nice.
- Yes! See? Did you see that? Yes!

684
00:46:51,911 --> 00:46:52,911
Settle down. All right.

685
00:46:52,971 --> 00:46:55,881
- Rock-paper-scissors! A tie. Again.
- All right.

686
00:46:55,941 --> 00:46:56,941
Rock-paper-scissors!

687
00:47:17,631 --> 00:47:19,401
(Veronica's Birthday)

688
00:47:31,551 --> 00:47:32,781
Good morning.

689
00:47:33,251 --> 00:47:37,281
Oh, my. But it's Sunday.
You both could've slept in.

690
00:47:37,921 --> 00:47:40,391
Wait, why the seaweed soup?
Is it someone's birthday?

691
00:47:40,921 --> 00:47:44,121
A birthday? No.
I just had a sudden craving for it.

692
00:47:44,291 --> 00:47:46,231
What?
But Mom, you hate seaweed soup.

693
00:47:46,391 --> 00:47:48,261
You can get a craving for it
every now and then.

694
00:47:48,801 --> 00:47:51,301
I love it. I love seaweed soup.
Anyway, I'll go wash up first.

695
00:47:51,801 --> 00:47:52,801
Okay.

696
00:47:53,371 --> 00:47:54,601
Min Seo, can you taste this for me?

697
00:47:55,241 --> 00:47:57,071
- Sure.
- Hold on.

698
00:48:06,781 --> 00:48:07,781
Hey, Min Seo.

699
00:48:09,181 --> 00:48:12,491
I'll watch the store alone tomorrow,
so you and Mom can take the day off.

700
00:48:12,921 --> 00:48:15,421
Or I can make myself scarce,
so you two can have the store alone.

701
00:48:17,321 --> 00:48:18,331
Hey.

702
00:48:18,691 --> 00:48:21,291
You barely touched your food.
What's wrong?

703
00:48:21,561 --> 00:48:25,531
Is it because you hate seaweed soup?
Americans don't eat it, right?

704
00:48:26,401 --> 00:48:28,641
- I do.
- What?

705
00:48:28,771 --> 00:48:30,141
I'm Korean.

706
00:48:30,901 --> 00:48:33,071
I'm not a big fan of seaweed soup,

707
00:48:35,381 --> 00:48:36,541
but I eat it on my birthday.

708
00:48:37,581 --> 00:48:39,811
Why do you look like
you're about to cry?

709
00:48:40,551 --> 00:48:41,551
It's just...

710
00:48:42,681 --> 00:48:44,251
today's my birthday.

711
00:48:45,321 --> 00:48:49,421
- What?
- I guess Mom must have remembered.

712
00:48:51,321 --> 00:48:52,861
Wow, I guess she did.

713
00:48:53,191 --> 00:48:56,061
Our mom really doesn't make
seaweed soup that often.

714
00:48:57,001 --> 00:48:58,501
Thank you so much, Eun Bin.

715
00:48:59,701 --> 00:49:00,831
Thanks to you,

716
00:49:01,201 --> 00:49:03,701
I finally got to have
my mom's birthday soup.

717
00:49:05,111 --> 00:49:08,241
This is truly
the best birthday gift ever.

718
00:49:13,211 --> 00:49:16,181
Min Seo, Happy birthday.

719
00:49:20,191 --> 00:49:24,061
(Shinna Snack Bar)

720
00:49:26,131 --> 00:49:27,131
Hello, sir.

721
00:49:27,731 --> 00:49:29,401
You don't have to worry anymore.

722
00:49:30,101 --> 00:49:32,171
I got the money for the surgery.

723
00:49:34,871 --> 00:49:35,871
I know, right?

724
00:49:36,241 --> 00:49:38,411
Thanks to a friend,
I was able to save my leg.

725
00:49:39,841 --> 00:49:43,011
Hold on, sir.
I'll buy you a nice meal.

726
00:49:45,111 --> 00:49:46,181
Oh, boy.

727
00:50:02,761 --> 00:50:04,631
Gosh, why did you all follow us out?

728
00:50:04,961 --> 00:50:07,731
I won rock-paper-scissors,
so I'm the designated guardian.

729
00:50:08,331 --> 00:50:12,571
Ju Ah, make sure she keeps doing
this arm exercise until the surgery,

730
00:50:12,741 --> 00:50:16,811
- so it hurts less later. Got it?
- Okay, roger that.

731
00:50:18,511 --> 00:50:23,081
- Honey...
- What? The surgery will go well,

732
00:50:23,121 --> 00:50:25,891
and that I should
just think happy thoughts?

733
00:50:26,691 --> 00:50:31,021
Yes. Why are you taking the words
right out of my mouth?

734
00:50:31,521 --> 00:50:33,991
You just worry about yourself.
And don't you dare cry.

735
00:50:35,101 --> 00:50:37,531
Who's crying? I wasn't crying.

736
00:50:38,331 --> 00:50:40,171
Keep us updated whenever you can,
all right?

737
00:50:40,501 --> 00:50:41,871
Don't worry, Uncle.

738
00:50:42,871 --> 00:50:45,041
Son, aren't you going to say bye?

739
00:50:52,881 --> 00:50:56,351
I'll be fine. Don't you worry, okay?

740
00:50:57,251 --> 00:50:58,321
Okay.

741
00:51:05,791 --> 00:51:09,261
Gosh, I can't with the men
in this family. Honestly.

742
00:51:09,661 --> 00:51:10,961
Tell me about it.

743
00:51:11,361 --> 00:51:14,601
I keep saying I'm fine.
Why is everyone being so dramatic?

744
00:51:15,571 --> 00:51:20,371
- Let's go.
- Okay. Grandma isn't coming.

745
00:51:20,911 --> 00:51:23,241
She said it feels too much
like a final goodbye.

746
00:51:23,681 --> 00:51:25,651
We had a long talk last night.

747
00:51:26,551 --> 00:51:28,851
Honey, make sure
you take good care of Mother.

748
00:51:29,621 --> 00:51:31,721
Yes, of course.

749
00:51:32,521 --> 00:51:33,521
I'm off.

750
00:51:33,851 --> 00:51:35,321
Hey, go on. Hurry up. Go.

751
00:51:35,991 --> 00:51:38,121
- Hey, you drive safe now.
- Yes. Be careful.

752
00:51:38,191 --> 00:51:40,961
- Go on, Seong Mi!
- Be safe. All right.

753
00:51:41,031 --> 00:51:42,031
Come back safe.

754
00:51:45,801 --> 00:51:46,901
Drive safe.

755
00:51:49,171 --> 00:51:51,641
You got this, Seong Mi! Yes!

756
00:52:06,951 --> 00:52:09,961
(Myungjin University Hospital)

757
00:52:16,661 --> 00:52:18,601
(Strict Bed Rest)

758
00:52:19,631 --> 00:52:20,631
What?

759
00:52:21,671 --> 00:52:25,911
It's quite a sight, seeing Korea's
most celebrated doctor lying here.

760
00:52:28,581 --> 00:52:31,811
Hey, I'm so glad
you won rock-paper-scissors.

761
00:52:32,381 --> 00:52:34,951
Tell me about it.
Dad, Uncle, and Woo Jae...

762
00:52:35,051 --> 00:52:38,321
- It would've been a total sob fest.
- Tell me about it.

763
00:52:39,651 --> 00:52:43,661
Gosh, I never thought I'd end up
in one of these gowns.

764
00:52:46,191 --> 00:52:50,261
Well, you're the prettiest person
I've seen in a hospital gown.

765
00:52:50,831 --> 00:52:52,131
You don't have to tell me.

766
00:52:53,901 --> 00:52:56,001
But you should
probably prepare yourself.

767
00:52:56,441 --> 00:53:00,711
My hair will fall out from chemo,
and it won't be a pretty sight.

768
00:53:01,071 --> 00:53:04,381
Why are you worrying about that now?
Just think positive!

769
00:53:07,411 --> 00:53:08,411
I'll go get you some water.

770
00:53:43,081 --> 00:53:45,751
(Patient Room)

771
00:53:52,461 --> 00:53:55,401
(Strict Bed Rest)

772
00:54:26,891 --> 00:54:29,961
(Taehan)

773
00:54:31,731 --> 00:54:32,831
I can't believe it.

774
00:54:35,301 --> 00:54:36,641
Hey, can you please sit down?

775
00:54:37,171 --> 00:54:38,741
Do I look like
I'm in any condition to sit?

776
00:54:39,071 --> 00:54:40,641
This is Paris we're talking about.
Paris!

777
00:54:41,071 --> 00:54:43,981
An offer for a two-month pop-up at
Clairmont Department Store in Paris!

778
00:54:44,041 --> 00:54:45,041
Yes!

779
00:54:45,281 --> 00:54:46,681
I also heard
Hyegyeong is considering...

780
00:54:46,681 --> 00:54:48,411
expanding us to all their locations.

781
00:54:49,021 --> 00:54:50,021
Incredible!

782
00:54:50,621 --> 00:54:53,751
With this kind of result,
not even Director Baek can stop us.

783
00:54:54,451 --> 00:54:55,461
And get this.

784
00:54:55,961 --> 00:54:59,691
You know they ran to the press
saying we forced Dr. Han's schedule?

785
00:55:00,261 --> 00:55:01,931
And that blew over in no time.

786
00:55:02,701 --> 00:55:04,931
Well, a baseless story like that
was never going to last.

787
00:55:06,471 --> 00:55:08,071
So why the long face, Pacu Nacho?

788
00:55:08,671 --> 00:55:09,671
Aren't you happy?

789
00:55:10,171 --> 00:55:13,471
Well, today is the day
of Dr. Han's surgery,

790
00:55:13,811 --> 00:55:15,381
so I'm a little worried.

791
00:55:17,411 --> 00:55:20,681
I'm sorry. That was tactless of me,
wasn't it?

792
00:55:24,551 --> 00:55:26,651
The surgery will go well.
It'll be over before you know it.

793
00:55:26,721 --> 00:55:29,291
Mom, don't be too nervous, okay?
It's okay. Don't be scared.

794
00:55:29,661 --> 00:55:33,191
- Ju Ah, what's gotten into you?
- I don't know. I'm the one shaking.

795
00:55:33,661 --> 00:55:35,161
Honestly.

796
00:55:37,731 --> 00:55:40,331
- Mother.
- Yes.

797
00:55:40,401 --> 00:55:43,401
Mother, I told you
you didn't have to come.

798
00:55:43,471 --> 00:55:46,541
Hey, I just couldn't bear
to stay home by myself.

799
00:55:46,971 --> 00:55:50,911
- Why? Afraid I wouldn't wake up?
- Don't say such things.

800
00:55:51,241 --> 00:55:52,751
You should watch what you say.

801
00:55:53,581 --> 00:55:55,981
I'm glad you came, Grandma.

802
00:55:56,421 --> 00:55:59,521
Of course.
I couldn't leave you by yourself.

803
00:56:01,521 --> 00:56:02,521
How are you feeling?

804
00:56:02,861 --> 00:56:04,221
- I'm fine.
- Good.

805
00:56:05,661 --> 00:56:07,131
We'll get you ready now.

806
00:56:07,661 --> 00:56:08,661
- Okay.
- Okay.

807
00:56:30,481 --> 00:56:32,191
It's going to be okay. Yes.

808
00:56:36,761 --> 00:56:38,831
(Operating Room)

809
00:56:38,891 --> 00:56:40,631
(Restricted Area)

810
00:56:40,691 --> 00:56:42,561
Don't you worry.
Everything will be fine. Okay?

811
00:56:48,501 --> 00:56:51,271
(Damga Charcoal Grill)

812
00:57:16,901 --> 00:57:18,901
(Surgery in Progress)

813
00:57:28,741 --> 00:57:31,941
(Operating Room)

814
00:57:43,691 --> 00:57:44,691
What?

815
00:57:47,391 --> 00:57:50,761
Dr. Han's surgery was a success.

816
00:57:51,101 --> 00:57:52,101
- Great!
- My gosh.

817
00:57:53,471 --> 00:57:56,001
I was so worried. What a relief.

818
00:57:56,441 --> 00:57:59,241
So, Dr. Han's surgery went well,

819
00:57:59,241 --> 00:58:00,941
and we landed the global contract.

820
00:58:01,341 --> 00:58:03,341
Now, we can get back to work
without a single worry.

821
00:58:03,711 --> 00:58:05,681
All right, then.

822
00:58:05,751 --> 00:58:08,051
Let's lock down the production line
for the initial order.

823
00:58:08,251 --> 00:58:13,121
Yes, I'll start by listing factories
and check our material supplies.

824
00:58:14,921 --> 00:58:18,361
Seeing how much you've all grown
makes me truly happy.

825
00:58:18,621 --> 00:58:21,031
We couldn't have done it
without you, Director.

826
00:58:21,631 --> 00:58:24,701
This is a result of
your own tireless efforts.

827
00:58:25,731 --> 00:58:26,731
Now...

828
00:58:27,401 --> 00:58:29,271
I feel like I can
leave things in your hands.

829
00:58:32,511 --> 00:58:34,071
- What?
- Is he leaving the company?

830
00:58:34,241 --> 00:58:35,711
What is he talking about?

831
00:58:39,051 --> 00:58:41,051
(Patient Chart: Han Seong Mi)

832
00:58:41,151 --> 00:58:43,221
(Strict Bed Rest)

833
00:58:47,021 --> 00:58:50,121
Do you think it's okay for her
to be sleeping this long?

834
00:58:50,961 --> 00:58:53,731
I'm not sure.
Should I go ask a nurse?

835
00:58:54,231 --> 00:58:55,231
Okay.

836
00:58:56,831 --> 00:58:58,661
(Strict Bed Rest)

837
00:59:01,131 --> 00:59:03,141
(906, Han Seong Mi)

838
00:59:09,211 --> 00:59:12,181
Director Yang decided to resign,
regardless of the show's outcome.

839
00:59:12,251 --> 00:59:13,481
You have to try and stop him, okay?

840
00:59:15,011 --> 00:59:16,021
What?

841
00:59:16,051 --> 00:59:18,051
(Intensive Care Unit)

842
00:59:38,871 --> 00:59:40,771
I'm glad her surgery went well.

843
00:59:45,181 --> 00:59:46,311
Are you leaving...

844
00:59:47,011 --> 00:59:48,251
because of me?

845
00:59:53,321 --> 00:59:54,321
You heard?

846
00:59:55,691 --> 00:59:57,491
Jun Hyeok told me.

847
00:59:58,121 --> 00:59:59,391
Even though everything went well,

848
00:59:59,961 --> 01:00:01,191
he said you're still leaving.

849
01:00:04,361 --> 01:00:05,401
I know I promised...

850
01:00:06,801 --> 01:00:09,001
to always be here for you.

851
01:00:11,101 --> 01:00:12,571
And I'm sorry...

852
01:00:13,771 --> 01:00:14,771
that I'm leaving.

853
01:00:15,941 --> 01:00:16,941
You just...

854
01:00:17,481 --> 01:00:18,941
can't bear to see me anymore?

855
01:00:24,851 --> 01:00:25,851
I just...

856
01:00:26,891 --> 01:00:29,891
care about your mother
and grandmother too much.

857
01:00:31,921 --> 01:00:33,331
I can't risk...

858
01:00:34,561 --> 01:00:35,801
hurting them anymore.

859
01:00:37,361 --> 01:00:39,071
But my mom and grandmother...

860
01:00:39,871 --> 01:00:41,471
They like you, too.

861
01:00:43,841 --> 01:00:44,871
I know.

862
01:00:53,711 --> 01:00:54,711
But still...

863
01:00:56,021 --> 01:00:57,721
I'm glad I came back.

864
01:00:58,351 --> 01:01:01,121
You know our fashion show
was a huge success, right?

865
01:01:03,661 --> 01:01:04,661
Yes.

866
01:01:06,661 --> 01:01:07,691
Congratulations.

867
01:01:15,271 --> 01:01:16,271
Can we...

868
01:01:17,401 --> 01:01:18,971
have one last...

869
01:01:19,971 --> 01:01:21,111
hug?

870
01:01:45,901 --> 01:01:46,971
I see.

871
01:01:47,271 --> 01:01:49,541
- Then how do I ask if they want...
- Yes.

872
01:01:49,841 --> 01:01:51,441
to pay in cash or by credit card?

873
01:01:52,001 --> 01:01:55,211
Oh, that's...
You can just read it right here.

874
01:01:55,511 --> 01:01:57,841
"Would you like to pay
by card or cash?"

875
01:02:01,681 --> 01:02:05,421
Or you could just simply say,
"Card or cash?"

876
01:02:06,721 --> 01:02:10,391
- Sorry.
- Was that your stomach growling?

877
01:02:11,361 --> 01:02:12,361
I guess so.

878
01:02:14,031 --> 01:02:15,061
Hang on a second.

879
01:02:18,531 --> 01:02:21,771
Here.
Go get yourself any snack you want.

880
01:02:22,031 --> 01:02:24,241
Thank you! I'll be right back.

881
01:02:24,301 --> 01:02:27,271
(Deep-Tissue Acupressure and Massage
for Spinal Muscles)

882
01:02:31,511 --> 01:02:36,351
Okay. "Would you like to pay by
card or cash?"

883
01:02:36,481 --> 01:02:39,491
"Card or cash?"

884
01:02:40,491 --> 01:02:42,491
(Mom)

885
01:02:52,631 --> 01:02:53,671
"Mom?"

886
01:02:59,371 --> 01:03:03,081
- Hello?
- Hello. Is this Veronica's phone?

887
01:03:03,741 --> 01:03:04,781
Excuse me?

888
01:03:05,141 --> 01:03:09,351
Isn't this Veronica's phone?
This is her mom.

889
01:03:09,721 --> 01:03:11,021
Veronica?

890
01:03:27,431 --> 01:03:28,531
About your wife...

891
01:03:30,271 --> 01:03:31,271
Go on.

892
01:03:31,941 --> 01:03:35,241
She wasn't having an affair.

893
01:03:37,041 --> 01:03:38,081
Really?

894
01:03:40,811 --> 01:03:41,851
That's a relief.

895
01:03:42,521 --> 01:03:45,581
Then why was she meeting
with that man?

896
01:03:45,891 --> 01:03:48,221
It seems they knew each other
from the past.

897
01:03:49,291 --> 01:03:50,491
The past?

898
01:03:50,961 --> 01:03:52,161
It's just...

899
01:03:52,761 --> 01:03:56,531
Sir, I'm not sure how much you know
about your wife's past,

900
01:03:57,131 --> 01:03:58,731
so this is a bit difficult
to bring up.

901
01:03:59,371 --> 01:04:00,571
I know everything.

902
01:04:01,601 --> 01:04:03,741
- You know her birth name, right?
- Of course.

903
01:04:04,171 --> 01:04:06,471
Jeong Sun. Im Jeong Sun.

904
01:04:08,171 --> 01:04:11,511
That she worked at a salon,
that she lived in an orphanage...

905
01:04:12,081 --> 01:04:13,151
I know all about it.

906
01:04:13,551 --> 01:04:15,451
I see. That's a relief.

907
01:04:16,451 --> 01:04:20,351
Kang Hyeon Cheol is a friend of hers
from the orphanage.

908
01:04:20,651 --> 01:04:22,991
He injured his leg
and needed surgery,

909
01:04:23,321 --> 01:04:25,861
and it seems your wife
helped him out financially.

910
01:04:27,761 --> 01:04:28,791
So that's what it was.

911
01:04:31,061 --> 01:04:33,601
I'm truly relieved.

912
01:04:33,831 --> 01:04:36,001
Tell me about it.
You have no idea how worried I was.

913
01:04:36,841 --> 01:04:38,341
Worried?

914
01:04:38,901 --> 01:04:40,041
Why would you be?

915
01:04:40,271 --> 01:04:44,581
Digging into her past, I found
she was an orphan with a new name.

916
01:04:44,641 --> 01:04:47,211
And she gave a child up
for adoption.

917
01:04:47,211 --> 01:04:48,481
All this stuff came out,

918
01:04:48,551 --> 01:04:49,581
so I couldn't help but worry...

919
01:04:49,581 --> 01:04:51,251
- Hold on.
- Yes?

920
01:04:52,421 --> 01:04:54,651
What did you just say?

921
01:04:55,191 --> 01:04:56,191
What?

922
01:04:57,361 --> 01:04:59,391
A child...

923
01:05:00,361 --> 01:05:01,391
She had a child?

924
01:05:02,761 --> 01:05:03,801
My Se Ri?

925
01:05:05,401 --> 01:05:07,301
You didn't know. What have I done?

926
01:05:07,571 --> 01:05:08,831
No, wait. Hey.

927
01:05:09,841 --> 01:05:12,271
Are you sure you're not mistaken?

928
01:05:12,871 --> 01:05:15,341
- No, it's just that...
- Is it true?

929
01:05:17,411 --> 01:05:19,041
Did my Se Ri really...

930
01:05:20,751 --> 01:05:21,881
have a child?

931
01:05:48,611 --> 01:05:51,381
(Recipe For Love)

932
01:05:51,441 --> 01:05:54,881
They said the cancer didn't spread
and the surgery went perfectly,

933
01:05:54,951 --> 01:05:57,381
but I'm so anxious,
like something has to be wrong.

934
01:05:58,751 --> 01:06:01,691
If she'd had a child,
how was she in a pageant?

935
01:06:02,591 --> 01:06:06,531
She said she'd save for her kid
to be a real mom to them someday.

936
01:06:07,861 --> 01:06:09,431
What am I going to do?

937
01:06:09,501 --> 01:06:12,531
She looks so down,
and she's barely said a word.

938
01:06:13,501 --> 01:06:16,841
I don't know.
I don't know what's going on.

939
01:06:17,906 --> 01:06:19,706
Dramaday.me
